<TITLE> Bush to lift ban on exploring for oil in OCS </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 WASHINGTON, Mon Jul 14,(bdnews24.com/Reuters) - President George W Bush plans to lift a ban on oil exploration in the Outer Continental Shelf and make a statement on energy needs, the White House said on Monday. "In his statement, the president will announce that he has decided to lift the executive ban on oil exploration in America's Outer Continental Shelf," White House spokeswoman Dana Perino said. "He'll again call on Congress to lift its legislative ban.
